            </span>
        </span>
    </p>

    <p class=MsoNormal>
        <span class=apple-converted-space>
            <span lang=EN-US
                  style='color:black;background:white'>
                Press “Yes” to send the text over the
                Internet. The text of the translated document will be opened in a new window of
                your browser:
            </span>
        </span>
    </p>

    <p class=MsoNormal>
        <img border=0 width=657 height=370 id="Picture 12"
             src="~/Content/Images/machine-translation/en/14.jpg">
    </p>

    <p class=MsoNormal>
        <span class=apple-converted-space>
            <span lang=EN-US
                  style='color:black;background:white'>
                The translation in MS Word is done from
                the source language into the target language chosen in the Translation Language
                Options. You can change these options by selecting <b>
                    Choose Translation
                    Language
                </b>from the <b>Translate</b> button:
            </span>
